WEBVTT

00:00.293 --> 00:02.520
<i>Previously on "Burden of Truth"...</i>

00:02.667 --> 00:04.146
Nobody knows how to make us better.

00:04.171 --> 00:05.280
She's spazzing!

00:05.305 --> 00:07.846
We're the freaks now,
the Twitching Girls of Millwood.

00:07.872 --> 00:10.459
<i>I am trying to land a job
with Billy Crawford</i>

00:10.484 --> 00:12.585
- and the city lawyer.
- <i>If we're not onto something,</i>

00:12.653 --> 00:14.420
<i>then why is someone following me?</i>

00:14.482 --> 00:16.768
The contamination's not coming
from any of the four sites.

00:16.841 --> 00:19.091
- Then where is it coming from?
- <i>The field itself.</i>

00:19.152 --> 00:21.435
- [MECHANICAL WHIRRING]
- [METALLIC CLANKING]

00:21.460 --> 00:24.362
Someone has buried toxic waste
in this field.

00:24.445 --> 00:25.988
You need to tell us
where that container

00:26.012 --> 00:27.537
is going after it's been excavated.

00:27.801 --> 00:30.269
[TIRES SCREECHING]

00:30.984 --> 00:33.652
- Hang on!
- [JOANNA GASPING]

00:35.977 --> 00:38.978
[TENSE ATMOSPHERIC MUSIC]

00:39.046 --> 00:40.980
♪ ♪

00:47.321 --> 00:49.121
We filed an Access
to Information request

00:49.190 --> 00:51.535
for the environmental records
of Matheson Steel.

00:51.568 --> 00:54.293
It's been ignored. We would
ask that the court compel

00:54.362 --> 00:57.131
Matheson Steel to comply with
their statutory obligations.

00:57.344 --> 00:59.298
To exonerate Matheson Steel

00:59.367 --> 01:02.535
and its parents company, we're
offering a detailed summary

01:02.560 --> 01:03.970
of our disposal policy.

01:04.038 --> 01:06.930
A carefully crafted
corporate smokescreen.

01:07.017 --> 01:10.018
I've written dozens of them.
If Matheson Steel

01:10.043 --> 01:13.012
has nothing to hide,
then show us the files.

01:13.037 --> 01:14.293
There's no proof that the barrels

01:14.317 --> 01:16.551
taken from the athletic field
belong to my client,

01:16.631 --> 01:18.740
and if Miss Hanley and Mr. Crawford

01:18.806 --> 01:20.762
would like access to my client's files,

01:20.787 --> 01:23.522
they can make their allegations
in a statement of claim.

01:25.639 --> 01:27.728
Councillors, do you have
sufficient evidence

01:27.753 --> 01:30.821
at present to file a lawsuit
against Matheson Steel?

01:31.095 --> 01:32.476
The barrels were removed

01:32.501 --> 01:35.717
from the field by a company
contracted to Matheson Steel

01:35.742 --> 01:37.402
at the direction of Ben Matheson.

01:37.427 --> 01:39.728
- I was doing my civic duty.
- Soil samples

01:39.753 --> 01:42.521
taken from the field
show traces of contaminants

01:42.546 --> 01:45.602
including benzene,
chlorine and methyl mercury.

01:45.732 --> 01:47.654
Chemicals don't have
fingerprints, Your Honour.

01:47.679 --> 01:49.268
There's no way to trace them
back to my client.

01:49.292 --> 01:52.066
Perhaps not. But this
particular grouping of chemicals

01:52.091 --> 01:54.650
is consistent with the ones
used in the manufacturing

01:54.675 --> 01:56.880
- of steel.
- My own daughter

01:56.914 --> 01:58.949
is one of the girls with this illness.

01:59.323 --> 02:01.245
- If I thought for one second...
- I represent

02:01.270 --> 02:03.567
the Matheson family in this matter.

02:04.094 --> 02:06.364
Ben's father Henry regrets that he's

02:06.389 --> 02:09.598
not able to attend,
but on my client's behalf,

02:09.734 --> 02:11.834
I request that the motion be denied.

02:12.809 --> 02:14.237
Sustainable waste management

02:14.262 --> 02:17.385
is very costly.
I imagine one could save

02:17.410 --> 02:19.559
upwards of hundreds
of thousands of dollars

02:19.584 --> 02:22.419
taking that waste
and dumping it oneself.

02:22.533 --> 02:24.765
Wouldn't you agree, Mr. Matheson?

02:31.794 --> 02:33.054
I'm sorry.

02:33.163 --> 02:35.331
This court denies your request.

02:36.367 --> 02:38.627
If you want to get to discovery,

02:38.696 --> 02:40.695
you need to file suit.

02:42.000 --> 02:48.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:55.045 --> 02:56.979
[THEME MUSIC]

02:57.047 --> 02:58.981
♪ ♪

03:04.561 --> 03:05.638
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

03:05.697 --> 03:08.654
- You're killing our jobs!
- Our kids are getting sick!

03:08.679 --> 03:10.613
You're taking money out of our pockets!

03:10.740 --> 03:13.899
- Matheson, I hope you rot in jail!
- Hey, go to hell!

03:13.924 --> 03:15.902
- That's enough, Jack.
- Our kids are being poisoned!

03:15.926 --> 03:17.617
They're not poisoned, they
did it to themselves!

03:17.641 --> 03:19.023
Probably some kind of drug overdose!

03:19.047 --> 03:20.144
Georgia's sick!

03:20.169 --> 03:21.837
She can barely get herself
out of bed in the morning!

03:21.861 --> 03:23.793
This has nothing to do with the mill!

03:23.818 --> 03:26.318
It's the mill keeping this town alive!

03:26.724 --> 03:29.376
- Wendy...
- You made your own daughter sick.

03:29.743 --> 03:32.177
- Hey! Get your hands off him!
- I did not do this!

03:33.091 --> 03:35.481
Come on. Let's do this
the right way. OK?

03:35.506 --> 03:37.017
- Easy, easy. Come on.
- He's threatening me?!

03:37.041 --> 03:40.576
- Back up. Come on.
- That's enough.

03:40.867 --> 03:43.668
- Molly!
- Oh, Molly!

03:43.724 --> 03:45.410
Hey, you OK?

03:46.363 --> 03:47.807
Yeah. I just...

03:47.875 --> 03:49.318
I couldn't get out of the way.

03:49.359 --> 03:52.278
It was like my brain
stopped talking to my body.

03:52.466 --> 03:53.967
It's OK. Let's get you out of here.

03:54.054 --> 03:56.087
Where's Luna? She said she'd be here.

03:56.317 --> 03:58.217
She's not answering my texts.

04:00.292 --> 04:01.887
Do you really think we can beat them?

04:02.599 --> 04:05.024
- Yeah.
- Then I'll do it.

04:05.081 --> 04:07.026
I'll be your named plaintiff.

04:07.094 --> 04:08.787
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

04:08.867 --> 04:11.648
I'm so sick of feeling powerless.

04:11.833 --> 04:13.866
[SOFT MUSIC]

04:13.934 --> 04:17.036
♪ ♪

04:22.695 --> 04:24.962
[DOG BARKING]

04:25.118 --> 04:28.022
Hiding the car keys? Real mature.

04:30.747 --> 04:33.554
There was a thing at the courthouse
that you just made me miss!

04:33.579 --> 04:35.168
My car, my call.

04:35.193 --> 04:38.032
There's no way I'm
missing Kookum's birthday too.

04:38.057 --> 04:39.291
What did I say, Luna?!

04:39.316 --> 04:41.469
I don't care! I'll find a ride.

04:41.696 --> 04:43.402
The whole family is gonna be there

04:43.427 --> 04:44.950
and we never get to see them.

04:45.065 --> 04:46.999
I don't want you hanging out with them!

04:47.497 --> 04:49.401
You don't know what it
was like for me there.

04:49.545 --> 04:52.513
- How they treated me.
- It's ancient history, Mom.

04:52.538 --> 04:54.257
They're different now.

04:54.844 --> 04:57.114
People don't change, Luna.

04:58.813 --> 05:00.746
My boss is gonna fire me!

05:01.685 --> 05:03.079
"Your boss"?

05:03.545 --> 05:04.918
She's not sticking around, you know.

05:04.942 --> 05:06.105
She's gonna leave you high and dry.

05:06.129 --> 05:07.276
But you don't even know her!

05:07.301 --> 05:08.979
Oh, I know her type.

05:11.180 --> 05:12.917
OK. Listen.

05:13.193 --> 05:14.381
Just come with me.

05:14.433 --> 05:16.795
I'm sure Kookum wants you there.

05:17.925 --> 05:19.072
If she'd have wanted me there,

05:19.096 --> 05:20.376
she would have asked me herself.

05:23.728 --> 05:25.097
[SIGHING]

05:31.412 --> 05:32.445
<i>Matheson's trying to bait us</i>

05:32.469 --> 05:33.685
into filing suit.

05:33.758 --> 05:35.193
They're hiding something.

05:35.811 --> 05:38.013
No, they just know
we don't have anything.

05:38.947 --> 05:40.719
Yet.

05:41.100 --> 05:42.468
Whoever ran us off the road

05:42.493 --> 05:43.929
clearly wants us to stop digging.

05:43.954 --> 05:45.776
Yeah, we made someone nervous.

05:45.955 --> 05:48.137
So we find who was driving the truck,

05:48.868 --> 05:50.631
we find that someone.

05:53.405 --> 05:54.767
Thank you for coming.

05:56.179 --> 05:57.488
What's he doing here?

05:57.513 --> 05:58.843
Millwood is my town,

05:58.868 --> 06:00.856
and I won't see it rip itself apart.

06:01.343 --> 06:04.143
We're capable of sorting out
our differences on our own.

06:04.437 --> 06:06.517
Ben has something he'd like
to say to the two of you.

06:06.762 --> 06:08.871
- Ben.
- I'm gonna pay to clean up

06:08.896 --> 06:10.182
the athletic field.

06:10.506 --> 06:11.723
Not the company.

06:11.953 --> 06:13.526
Me, personally.

06:13.822 --> 06:16.305
Is that an admission of guilt?

06:16.798 --> 06:18.111
No.

06:19.157 --> 06:21.945
I can't have people
thinking that I did this.

06:22.203 --> 06:23.821
This is my home.

06:24.359 --> 06:27.694
We all know how important
the mill is. The city accepts.

06:28.991 --> 06:32.798
- What is the offer, exactly?
- He's going to clean the field.

06:32.987 --> 06:34.290
In exchange for what?

06:34.789 --> 06:36.666
You're gonna drop all this nonsense.

06:37.078 --> 06:38.428
Drop the case?

06:38.453 --> 06:41.388
- That's right.
- It's time to move on.

06:45.994 --> 06:48.562
♪ ♪

06:56.051 --> 06:59.639
[MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

06:59.708 --> 07:01.842
♪ ♪

07:03.365 --> 07:04.727
Hey.

07:06.621 --> 07:09.163
That was pretty crazy today. You OK?

07:09.618 --> 07:12.285
Yeah, I can take a hit.

07:14.455 --> 07:16.322
What's good?

07:16.490 --> 07:18.491
Everything.

07:20.183 --> 07:22.059
I just wanted to see
if you were all right.

07:22.084 --> 07:23.458
I'm good.

07:23.801 --> 07:25.553
Maybe you shouldn't
be back at work already.

07:25.578 --> 07:27.939
Well, that's not how jobs work.

07:30.626 --> 07:32.593
I haven't been back here in forever.

07:32.681 --> 07:35.148
Not fancy enough
for the Mathesons anymore?

07:36.034 --> 07:37.424
Are you mad at me?

07:38.029 --> 07:39.426
You were on the wrong side today.

07:39.759 --> 07:42.199
My dad didn't do this. I'm sick too!

07:42.245 --> 07:44.033
Dude, we stood there and watched them

07:44.058 --> 07:45.313
pull barrels out of the field!

07:45.385 --> 07:46.958
That doesn't prove anything.

07:47.155 --> 07:48.465
Whatever.

07:48.745 --> 07:50.562
Everyone knows he's guilty anyway.

07:50.606 --> 07:52.097
He's not!

07:52.194 --> 07:54.895
So tell your uncle
to stop spreading lies.

07:57.733 --> 07:59.434
Hi, Miss Evans.

08:00.103 --> 08:02.123
I called for a pickup.

08:06.055 --> 08:08.327
Two orders of chicken fingers.

08:09.474 --> 08:12.191
One day, when all this is behind you,

08:12.471 --> 08:14.528
you'll both have kids
and you'll both be too tired

08:14.553 --> 08:17.621
to do anything but bring home
takeout chicken fingers.

08:22.223 --> 08:24.034
It's nice to see you back at work.

08:27.536 --> 08:29.866
No one else knows
what you're going through.

08:31.467 --> 08:33.957
No matter what,
you're in this together.

08:36.052 --> 08:39.120
♪ ♪

08:55.223 --> 08:56.727
[INDISTINCT SPEAKING OVER RADIO]

08:57.983 --> 08:59.440
- Hey.
- Hey.

08:59.816 --> 09:02.142
I had a chat with Pat Collins.

09:03.418 --> 09:05.479
Still workin' off a cheat sheet, huh?

09:05.950 --> 09:07.815
- Just like high school.
- Huh.

09:08.679 --> 09:10.484
Captain of the hockey team

09:10.552 --> 09:12.535
teasing the slightly chubby A.V. nerd,

09:12.560 --> 09:15.152
- exactly like high school.
- Come on, you weren't that fat.

09:15.177 --> 09:18.412
Oh, watch it, Crawford.
I grew into my chubbiness.

09:18.437 --> 09:20.303
What did Pat Collins have to say?

09:20.977 --> 09:22.363
Well, his alibi for the night

09:22.431 --> 09:24.084
you were run off the road checks out,

09:24.109 --> 09:27.307
and he has a receipt for the
sale of the truck to this place.

09:28.260 --> 09:30.237
Let's see if it's legit.

09:30.305 --> 09:32.319
[MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO]

09:32.568 --> 09:35.040
Hey. You the owner?

09:36.379 --> 09:39.428
Russ... You guys here about the truck?

09:39.632 --> 09:41.725
Wondered if we could
take a look at your records,

09:41.750 --> 09:44.002
ensure that the vehicle
in question was scrapped.

09:44.286 --> 09:46.720
Too good to get rid of.
Figured I'd fix her up.

09:47.423 --> 09:48.952
She's out back.

09:59.682 --> 10:01.649
Quite the collection you've got.

10:02.949 --> 10:04.605
Aw, man!

10:06.021 --> 10:07.595
It was right here!

10:10.767 --> 10:12.363
When was the last time
you saw the vehicle?

10:12.387 --> 10:14.186
Days... A week, maybe.

10:14.211 --> 10:16.066
You don't lock the yard up after hours?

10:16.091 --> 10:17.255
Never had to.

10:17.667 --> 10:19.094
Not 'til now.

10:22.056 --> 10:23.562
Now what?

10:28.210 --> 10:31.177
[SOFT MUSIC]

10:31.266 --> 10:33.934
♪ ♪

10:51.420 --> 10:54.622
♪ ♪

10:57.112 --> 10:59.112
[SIGHING]

11:12.542 --> 11:14.709
♪ ♪

11:31.860 --> 11:33.861
♪ ♪

11:52.481 --> 11:54.548
♪ ♪

12:14.002 --> 12:15.936
♪ ♪

12:24.132 --> 12:26.099
[KNOCKING]

12:28.266 --> 12:30.200
[SIGHING]

12:33.364 --> 12:35.497
Apology pizza?

12:36.003 --> 12:38.145
Does it come with
apology garlic fingers?

12:38.427 --> 12:40.328
I wish.

12:41.638 --> 12:44.048
Luna, you can't just
disappear on me like that.

12:44.494 --> 12:45.841
I know. I'm sorry.

12:46.627 --> 12:48.091
Molly's pissed at me too.

12:48.304 --> 12:49.711
Where were you?

12:50.304 --> 12:52.103
My mom hid the car keys.

12:52.276 --> 12:54.449
Did she hide your cell phone too?

12:54.764 --> 12:56.230
Usually she has a freak out,

12:56.273 --> 12:57.914
I ride it out and it passes.

12:58.324 --> 12:59.888
You missed our motion hearing.

12:59.956 --> 13:02.491
I know. I wanted to be there.

13:03.707 --> 13:04.997
Did we win?

13:05.194 --> 13:07.062
No, we didn't.

13:11.875 --> 13:13.809
[SIGHING]

13:15.733 --> 13:17.833
What was the fight about?

13:19.503 --> 13:21.309
It's my kookum's birthday tomorrow.

13:21.763 --> 13:23.404
My mom and her don't get along,

13:23.460 --> 13:25.660
so apparently we aren't going.

13:26.172 --> 13:28.050
Sounds like your family
loves Mother's Day

13:28.118 --> 13:30.552
about as much as I do.

13:31.545 --> 13:32.921
Does she live in town?

13:32.989 --> 13:35.057
Long Grass First Nation.

13:37.405 --> 13:40.022
Why are we looking at
partnerships from 20 years ago?

13:40.188 --> 13:42.552
Well, because our hydrologist

13:42.577 --> 13:44.257
thinks that's
when the barrels were buried.

13:44.345 --> 13:45.873
We need to find evidence

13:45.898 --> 13:48.470
that links the barrels to the mill.

13:49.966 --> 13:51.840
- You just need a lift out there?
- Yeah.

13:53.576 --> 13:54.984
I can drive you.

13:55.531 --> 13:56.945
Are you serious?

13:57.201 --> 13:59.448
Yeah. We can work in the car.

13:59.516 --> 14:01.349
Yeah. Of course.

14:02.619 --> 14:03.701
So...

14:03.726 --> 14:05.387
why partnerships?

14:05.887 --> 14:07.844
I want to find everybody

14:07.869 --> 14:09.658
that Matheson Steel has worked with.

14:10.442 --> 14:13.052
Ben Matheson's dad Henry
was in charge then,

14:13.077 --> 14:14.729
so keep an eye out for that name also.

14:14.754 --> 14:16.065
On it.

14:25.507 --> 14:27.175
Why is my gut still telling me

14:27.200 --> 14:28.968
it was Pat Collins driving that truck?

14:29.060 --> 14:30.801
It could be the wings.

14:31.735 --> 14:34.663
Collins was home with his
wife, Brandy. She confirmed it.

14:34.756 --> 14:36.885
Doesn't he have a record
for domestic assault?

14:37.071 --> 14:38.426
So he threatens to get rough,

14:38.451 --> 14:40.406
she's gonna say whatever
he wants her to say.

14:40.559 --> 14:42.539
She does have a part-time job
at the mill.

14:42.679 --> 14:44.520
That guy's not gonna run
somebody off the road

14:44.545 --> 14:46.518
to save his girl's part-time job.

14:46.906 --> 14:48.101
What about his brother?

14:48.126 --> 14:50.654
- Tim?
- He's a foreman at the mill.

14:50.868 --> 14:52.791
And he's got three kids.

14:54.659 --> 14:56.028
You got a spare key to your car?

14:56.053 --> 14:58.306
- Yeah.
- Me too.

14:59.429 --> 15:00.886
So you sell your truck to a place

15:00.911 --> 15:03.055
you know you'd have
access to it afterward,

15:03.401 --> 15:05.847
give the spare key
to your brother, he steals it.

15:06.851 --> 15:08.552
Nah. Collins doesn't strike me

15:08.577 --> 15:09.618
as the type to be smart enough

15:09.642 --> 15:10.987
to cook up a plan like that.

15:11.577 --> 15:13.388
Ben might be, though.

15:13.514 --> 15:15.103
I know you don't want
to entertain it, but...

15:15.127 --> 15:16.765
He coached my high school hockey team.

15:16.790 --> 15:19.281
He was a master of
intimidation on the ice.

15:19.585 --> 15:22.015
May be time to have a
chat with Tim Collins.

15:22.140 --> 15:23.461
I'll talk to Ben.

15:23.905 --> 15:26.064
One-on-one. No lawyers.

15:26.191 --> 15:29.004
- Uh...
- You know what I mean.

15:29.471 --> 15:31.188
Just don't go in with any bias,

15:31.213 --> 15:32.648
first rule of interrogation.

15:32.859 --> 15:34.910
I'm just gonna talk to the guy.

15:35.565 --> 15:37.470
[SOFT MUSIC]

15:37.700 --> 15:40.568
♪ ♪

15:42.096 --> 15:44.531
[BIRDS CHIRPING OUTSIDE]

15:51.241 --> 15:52.941
[SHARP INTAKE OF BREATH]

16:11.680 --> 16:14.648
[PHONE RINGING]

16:18.270 --> 16:19.825
Hey. I need your help.

16:19.850 --> 16:21.650
<i>And a good morning to you too.</i>

16:22.008 --> 16:24.166
Old barrels were found
in the athletic field.

16:24.191 --> 16:26.188
Finger's pointing to Matheson Steel.

16:27.334 --> 16:29.346
The firm said "no" on this, Joanna.

16:29.463 --> 16:31.482
<i>I'm not asking the firm.</i>

16:32.171 --> 16:33.908
I'm asking you.

16:34.580 --> 16:36.514
<i>How well did you know Henry Matheson?</i>

16:36.662 --> 16:38.729
Not well. We golfed
together a few times.

16:39.377 --> 16:41.916
Has the plant ever
had a spill or an accident?

16:42.023 --> 16:43.210
<i>That's not exactly the kind of thing</i>

16:43.234 --> 16:44.948
<i>you talk about in the clubhouse.</i>

16:44.973 --> 16:46.054
But I'll tell you one thing.

16:46.078 --> 16:48.286
The Matheson family
singlehandedly saved that town.

16:48.395 --> 16:50.462
You always say
"I'll tell you one thing"

16:50.487 --> 16:52.124
when you're holding something back.

16:52.149 --> 16:54.957
You're reading my tells now?
I might've taught you too well.

16:55.066 --> 16:56.448
So what aren't you saying?

16:56.473 --> 16:57.793
When everyone else was outsourcing

16:57.817 --> 16:59.171
to cut down on labour costs,

16:59.196 --> 17:00.497
the Matheson family was the one

17:00.522 --> 17:01.532
that poured everything they had

17:01.556 --> 17:03.886
<i>- back into that mill.</i>
- Until there was nothing left

17:03.911 --> 17:06.512
and they had to sell to PNL Steel.

17:07.419 --> 17:09.540
They could've cut corners trying

17:09.566 --> 17:11.429
<i>to make the deal more attractive.</i>

17:11.691 --> 17:13.891
Are you into your savings
on this thing?

17:15.280 --> 17:16.493
No.

17:16.540 --> 17:18.099
<i>I'm worried about you, Joanna.</i>

17:18.145 --> 17:21.065
The partners are talking.
<i>You need to come back home.</i>

17:21.165 --> 17:23.133
Not until I have a win.

17:30.728 --> 17:31.935
Is everything OK?

17:31.960 --> 17:33.155
Yeah.

17:33.612 --> 17:35.215
Still need a lift to the reserve?

17:35.301 --> 17:37.135
You mind if we stop at my house first?

17:37.223 --> 17:39.224
I need to get something.

17:40.874 --> 17:42.908
[SIGHING]

17:44.322 --> 17:46.089
[DOOR CREAKING]

17:55.783 --> 17:57.556
Where have you been?

17:59.996 --> 18:01.216
I was working.

18:01.260 --> 18:02.769
I texted you.

18:07.513 --> 18:09.447
Guess this means you're going.

18:10.082 --> 18:12.982
- She's my grandmother.
- Who's driving you?

18:13.040 --> 18:15.803
- Your boss?
- What do you have against her?

18:15.828 --> 18:17.682
She's driving me
to Kookum's birthday party.

18:17.707 --> 18:20.135
- It's not a big deal.
- If you take her to that party,

18:20.160 --> 18:22.860
it's not gonna end well.
She's not one of us.

18:23.035 --> 18:25.878
And I'm not gonna be responsible
for the storm she brings!

18:26.638 --> 18:28.623
Oh, you wanna act
like I'm not your mother?

18:28.722 --> 18:31.901
Go ahead. She can have the job.
It's all hers.

18:37.649 --> 18:39.649
[DOOR CLOSING]

18:44.310 --> 18:45.812
Damn it.

18:55.695 --> 18:58.029
♪ ♪

19:09.969 --> 19:12.289
So, basically what I'm saying
is that it's a deadlock

19:12.314 --> 19:14.383
until we file our statement
of claim against the company.

19:14.407 --> 19:17.074
They're either gonna... wanna settle

19:17.137 --> 19:19.170
or drown us in paperwork,

19:19.205 --> 19:21.406
but it's the only way
for us to move forward.

19:25.017 --> 19:27.451
- Luna?
- Yeah, sorry. What?

19:29.149 --> 19:32.683
You've obviously got
something on your mind.

19:34.040 --> 19:35.866
I'm a good listener.

19:35.934 --> 19:38.602
Lawyer-client privilege and all that.

19:41.621 --> 19:43.588
It's exhausting.

19:44.789 --> 19:46.487
What is?

19:47.506 --> 19:50.066
Trying to take the high road
all the time.

19:51.124 --> 19:53.130
Yeah, well, you're gonna
have to stop doing that

19:53.155 --> 19:54.955
if you wanna be a lawyer.

19:59.920 --> 20:03.421
It was always the high road
with my mom.

20:03.835 --> 20:06.403
She really liked rules.

20:06.613 --> 20:09.748
And she wasn't great with affection.

20:11.125 --> 20:13.158
Definitely not maternal.

20:16.355 --> 20:18.456
Maybe that's why she left.

20:21.134 --> 20:23.134
My dad left too.

20:23.974 --> 20:25.367
He left before

20:25.392 --> 20:27.358
the pee was even dry on the stick.

20:29.368 --> 20:31.769
My mom was so young, you know?

20:33.165 --> 20:34.958
It's just been hard.

20:35.061 --> 20:36.788
I bet.

20:36.848 --> 20:38.415
Yeah.

20:40.912 --> 20:42.779
What's your dad like?

20:43.502 --> 20:44.712
He's great...

20:44.812 --> 20:47.202
most of the time, you
know, when he's...

20:47.227 --> 20:50.009
not trying to out-manoeuvre me.

20:50.675 --> 20:52.809
The problem is I know all his tells.

20:53.112 --> 20:55.910
- Tells?
- These things he does

20:55.935 --> 20:58.306
that let me know when he's
being less than honest.

20:58.397 --> 21:00.106
Like what?

21:00.180 --> 21:01.531
I don't know, like he...

21:01.556 --> 21:03.640
yawns before he says something.

21:04.063 --> 21:06.715
"What'd you get up to last night, Dad?"

21:07.019 --> 21:09.842
"Oh, you know, I just had
a few drinks at the club."

21:11.425 --> 21:14.426
Or "I'll tell you one thing."

21:14.574 --> 21:17.590
- That's another classic.
- Nice.

21:18.298 --> 21:21.399
I'm gonna start looking for
Molly's tells. And yours.

21:23.176 --> 21:25.552
Oh, God. I've created a monster.

21:39.545 --> 21:41.778
So, what? Are you stalking me now?

21:41.860 --> 21:43.794
No.

21:44.505 --> 21:46.363
I wanted to say something.

21:46.431 --> 21:49.066
It just took me a while
to figure it out.

21:50.937 --> 21:54.586
- I'm not apologizing.
- Well, that was worth the wait.

21:54.894 --> 21:57.895
- Look, we're sick.
- Yeah, thanks to your dad!

21:57.920 --> 22:00.255
We don't know that.

22:01.940 --> 22:03.555
But whatever this turns out to be,

22:03.635 --> 22:05.969
it doesn't change the fact
that we both have it.

22:06.718 --> 22:08.307
And Miss Evans was right.

22:08.374 --> 22:09.974
At the end of the day,

22:10.595 --> 22:12.089
this is who we are.

22:12.437 --> 22:14.370
It doesn't matter how we got here.

22:16.842 --> 22:19.590
Last night, I woke up
in the middle of the night.

22:19.725 --> 22:22.392
- Scared?
- No. I had to pee.

22:22.514 --> 22:24.748
And so I got up,

22:24.773 --> 22:27.373
opened the bathroom door and twitched,

22:28.401 --> 22:30.369
whacked myself in the head

22:30.397 --> 22:32.070
and nearly knocked myself out.

22:33.652 --> 22:35.777
Put me back on the field, Coach!
I think I'm ready!

22:35.802 --> 22:38.530
- Ugh, that's terrible.
- Yeah.

22:41.465 --> 22:43.266
Let's go.

22:44.071 --> 22:45.179
Last week, I, um,

22:45.204 --> 22:46.478
I tried to make spaghetti sauce.

22:46.502 --> 22:47.583
I got it everywhere.

22:47.714 --> 22:49.767
It looked like <i> Saw 3D</i> in my kitchen.

22:49.792 --> 22:51.872
- Oh, my God.
- If I hear my mom say

22:51.897 --> 22:54.597
"you're gonna be fine"
just one more time...

22:54.622 --> 22:56.042
Yeah, I know. Or "get well soon."

22:56.067 --> 22:58.875
Like you can just sleep it off
like it's some bad cold.

22:59.651 --> 23:02.039
- Wouldn't that be nice.
- Yeah.

23:02.107 --> 23:03.246
Look, like me or not,

23:03.271 --> 23:04.752
we're in this together.

23:09.961 --> 23:11.995
♪ ♪

23:24.009 --> 23:25.943
[NEIGHING]

23:40.698 --> 23:42.965
[BARKING]

23:56.094 --> 23:58.529
♪ ♪

24:08.007 --> 24:10.140
♪ ♪

24:23.735 --> 24:25.669
I can't wait for them to meet you.

24:33.581 --> 24:36.433
- Kookum!
- Luna!

24:36.789 --> 24:39.364
- Happy birthday!
- Would you look who it is!

24:39.551 --> 24:41.772
Joanna, this is my cousin, Susan.

24:42.114 --> 24:44.408
Kookum. This is my boss.

24:44.696 --> 24:46.663
Joanna Hanley.

24:49.254 --> 24:50.654
Where's your mom?

24:50.715 --> 24:53.285
She had one of her migraines,
but she sends her love.

24:54.397 --> 24:57.921
It's a really beautiful spot
you guys have out here.

25:01.827 --> 25:04.895
Joanna's been teaching me
all about environmental law.

25:05.486 --> 25:08.799
Yes, she is a very smart young woman.

25:12.837 --> 25:15.122
Um... I should probably
get back to work.

25:15.147 --> 25:16.824
Stay... There's lots of food.

25:16.849 --> 25:18.103
Right, Kookum?

25:18.191 --> 25:21.752
You're too thin, Luna. Has
your mother been feeding you?

25:21.907 --> 25:23.526
She still on those night shifts?

25:23.551 --> 25:25.646
She works hard and we
take care of each other.

25:25.731 --> 25:28.436
Don't mind her. She's just getting old.

25:29.387 --> 25:31.321
I'm just gonna go wash my hands.

25:31.736 --> 25:34.671
- Kitchen's just inside the front door.
- Thank you.

25:37.370 --> 25:39.403
[SOFT MUSIC]

25:39.831 --> 25:41.932
♪ ♪

25:58.650 --> 26:00.650
[SIGHING]

26:20.665 --> 26:23.585
My granddaughter seems
quite taken with you.

26:26.012 --> 26:28.011
She's pretty special.

26:28.327 --> 26:30.594
An activist at heart, I think.

26:31.507 --> 26:33.350
Always had an opinion,

26:33.396 --> 26:35.377
just like her mother.

26:35.554 --> 26:37.526
Her first word was "no."

26:38.183 --> 26:41.150
Well, I look forward to meeting her.

26:42.702 --> 26:45.046
How is it that Luna
came to work for you?

26:45.901 --> 26:48.560
She wanted to help out
her friend, Molly.

26:48.585 --> 26:51.180
She's also been a big help on the case.

26:51.269 --> 26:53.136
Your idea?

26:53.438 --> 26:55.023
All Luna.

26:57.924 --> 27:00.625
We appreciate you bringing her out,

27:00.772 --> 27:02.939
but it may be best if you got going.

27:03.049 --> 27:05.082
Not everyone here takes to outsiders.

27:09.488 --> 27:12.501
Yeah... of course.

27:27.579 --> 27:29.852
Ben. Thank you for agreeing to meet me.

27:30.009 --> 27:31.739
I would've ordered a pitcher
but I didn't know

27:31.763 --> 27:33.577
what the legal ramifications would be.

27:36.014 --> 27:39.768
- Look, I'm here as a friend.
- Come on, man.

27:39.944 --> 27:43.145
What you're accusing me of?
Friends don't do that.

27:48.460 --> 27:50.493
I'm not accusing you of anything.

27:51.094 --> 27:52.896
I'm just here to talk.

27:53.291 --> 27:54.774
So talk.

28:06.611 --> 28:08.284
Luna, I got a call.

28:08.359 --> 28:10.193
It's work. I've gotta go.

28:10.415 --> 28:11.700
Do you want me to come back
and pick you up?

28:11.724 --> 28:13.706
We'll make sure she gets home.

28:15.487 --> 28:18.469
Thanks for bringing me.
And call me if you need me.

28:18.976 --> 28:21.264
She can manage a day without you.

28:24.289 --> 28:26.638
- Bye.
- Bye.

28:31.263 --> 28:33.063
I'm not saying you knew
about the barrels.

28:33.252 --> 28:36.490
The Crawford I knew,
the Crawford I coached,

28:36.675 --> 28:38.151
that guy's not sitting right across

28:38.176 --> 28:39.775
from me right now, slinging this bile.

28:39.800 --> 28:41.568
All I'm asking is, is it possible

28:41.593 --> 28:43.050
that this happened before your time?

28:43.179 --> 28:44.752
So you're blaming my dad now?

28:44.777 --> 28:47.105
I'm not blaming anyone. I'm asking.

28:47.972 --> 28:49.553
As a friend.

28:50.060 --> 28:52.315
Believe it or not,
I am trying to protect you.

28:52.512 --> 28:55.313
Environmental laws back then,
they weren't what they are today.

28:56.645 --> 28:59.133
You come after anyone in my family,

28:59.215 --> 29:01.035
you're coming after me.

29:03.502 --> 29:06.202
I paid for the barrel
extraction, Billy.

29:06.452 --> 29:07.878
I did that. No one else.

29:07.905 --> 29:09.067
That doesn't preclude the fact

29:09.091 --> 29:10.557
that the chemicals
line up with the mill.

29:10.581 --> 29:12.681
- Ugh! Come on!
- Ben. Ben!

29:12.711 --> 29:15.755
You are talking about my
daughter, here. And your niece!

29:15.780 --> 29:18.615
- That's why this is so hard.
- Not to mention my crew.

29:19.363 --> 29:21.602
Do you think that I would
knowingly hurt them?

29:21.627 --> 29:23.487
I would do anything for those guys!

29:23.622 --> 29:25.074
Anything?

29:26.637 --> 29:28.729
What's that supposed to mean, Billy?

29:30.636 --> 29:33.103
You hear about that truck
that ran us off the road?

29:33.585 --> 29:36.955
So, what? You're accusing
me of that now, too?

29:39.250 --> 29:40.859
You are.

29:44.610 --> 29:47.277
People are scared of losing their jobs.

29:47.879 --> 29:49.212
I get that.

29:50.295 --> 29:51.659
Tim Collins, he would do anything

29:51.684 --> 29:52.885
to support his family.

29:53.255 --> 29:55.045
What's Tim got to do with any of this?

29:55.070 --> 29:56.103
I hope nothing,

29:56.128 --> 29:58.028
but Beckbie is over there right now.

30:00.725 --> 30:03.492
Is it possible the barrels
fell off a truck?

30:03.517 --> 30:04.825
That there was some kind of accident?

30:04.849 --> 30:06.816
You are way out of line.

30:07.266 --> 30:09.266
Something happened here, Ben.

30:09.303 --> 30:11.711
You cannot just
bury your head in the sand.

30:12.091 --> 30:14.091
[SCOFFING]

30:15.741 --> 30:17.574
Screw you, Crawford.

30:17.875 --> 30:19.709
We're done.

30:20.032 --> 30:21.998
[TENSE MUSIC]

30:22.414 --> 30:24.348
♪ ♪

30:32.724 --> 30:35.692
♪ ♪

30:44.951 --> 30:46.524
What are you doing here?

30:46.617 --> 30:48.451
So this is where you've
been working, huh?

30:48.944 --> 30:50.854
I wrote the statement of claim.

30:51.203 --> 30:53.443
We're making a case against
Matheson Steel.

30:54.489 --> 30:56.993
When you decide to do
something, you go all the way.

30:57.324 --> 30:59.039
The problem is you don't
know when to let go.

30:59.063 --> 31:01.938
Seriously, why are you here?

31:02.085 --> 31:04.113
Because you sounded crazy on the phone.

31:05.020 --> 31:07.263
A male partner does this
and he's showing initiative.

31:07.288 --> 31:09.847
A female does the exact same
thing and she's "crazy."

31:09.887 --> 31:11.574
Give me a break, Joanna.

31:11.856 --> 31:13.866
There were barrels in the ground!

31:20.691 --> 31:22.691
[SIGHING]

31:27.730 --> 31:29.439
This is how I work.

31:35.166 --> 31:37.101
It's not as insane as it looks.

31:37.174 --> 31:39.894
- [SCOFFING]
- Let me prove it to you.

31:41.672 --> 31:43.639
[OMINOUS ATMOSPHERIC MUSIC]

31:43.841 --> 31:45.841
♪ ♪

31:51.761 --> 31:53.349
I get it.

31:53.941 --> 31:55.217
It's tragic,

31:55.421 --> 31:57.854
but it's not your job to fix it.

31:58.450 --> 31:59.946
These people are counting on me.

31:59.971 --> 32:01.978
You can't file a lawsuit on a hunch.

32:02.058 --> 32:03.242
You know that.

32:03.324 --> 32:05.247
I know that if I
can figure out how they

32:05.272 --> 32:08.299
got in there, I can
find a direct link to the mill.

32:08.400 --> 32:10.610
Sweetheart, emotions
cloud your judgment.

32:10.635 --> 32:12.444
It affects your choices.

32:15.699 --> 32:17.600
Why did you lie to me about Mom?

32:24.658 --> 32:26.327
Ahem.

32:27.661 --> 32:28.791
Um...

32:28.859 --> 32:31.360
I was just trying to protect you.

32:32.887 --> 32:35.465
She was growing more and
more withdrawn by the day.

32:35.490 --> 32:38.079
I was afraid of what that might
do to you in the long run.

32:38.378 --> 32:39.851
She needed help.

32:40.418 --> 32:44.206
And I did my best, but... I failed her.

32:49.160 --> 32:51.457
Maybe I failed you too, so...

32:57.613 --> 32:59.413
No, Dad. You didn't fail me.

33:00.495 --> 33:02.161
I'm fine.

33:05.373 --> 33:08.896
Look, even if the mill did all this,

33:08.958 --> 33:10.502
it was decades ago.

33:10.572 --> 33:12.933
These cases are so difficult to prove.

33:13.755 --> 33:15.729
Sweetheart, you did everything right.

33:15.798 --> 33:17.131
Matheson offered to clean up.

33:17.156 --> 33:19.124
That's a win. A big one!

33:20.976 --> 33:23.347
I'm proud of you, and I want you

33:23.372 --> 33:25.129
back on my team.

33:26.166 --> 33:28.042
Let the Crawford kid write the wills

33:28.044 --> 33:30.177
for this... dying town.

33:35.584 --> 33:38.045
So when can I expect you
back at the office?

33:48.664 --> 33:51.663
I have a few things
I have to wrap up first.

33:53.522 --> 33:57.505
OK. Yes. OK. That's my girl.

34:14.137 --> 34:16.150
Kookum sent you a pie.

34:19.373 --> 34:21.739
Everybody asked about you. I told them

34:21.764 --> 34:23.266
you had a migraine.

34:25.853 --> 34:27.145
Mom?

34:27.170 --> 34:28.976
Do you want some pie?

34:29.183 --> 34:31.809
No, I don't want pie.

34:32.995 --> 34:34.661
But it doesn't seem to matter
what I want. You're gonna

34:34.685 --> 34:35.859
go and do whatever you want.

34:35.884 --> 34:37.380
That's not true.

34:42.217 --> 34:44.851
What if I said I don't want
you working for her anymore?

34:45.156 --> 34:47.295
Hmm? You wanna work?

34:47.402 --> 34:48.704
I'll get you a job at the mill.

34:48.728 --> 34:50.098
There's an opening for a night cleaner.

34:50.121 --> 34:51.725
I don't wanna work at the mill.

34:51.793 --> 34:54.411
That mill has put dinner
on this table your whole life!

34:54.437 --> 34:56.304
Yeah, I'm not saying that it hasn't!

34:56.353 --> 34:59.500
Oh, so she comes to town
and now you're too good for it?

34:59.595 --> 35:03.139
- She's messing with us, Luna!
- How?

35:04.199 --> 35:06.707
You know what? Forget it.

35:06.775 --> 35:08.533
I'll take care of this myself.

35:08.576 --> 35:11.559
What are you talking about? Mom!

35:11.685 --> 35:13.560
Where are you going?

35:17.105 --> 35:18.185
[SIGHING]

35:18.253 --> 35:20.187
[DOOR BELL JINGLING]

35:20.998 --> 35:23.191
Where've you been?
I've been calling you.

35:23.525 --> 35:24.892
Yeah, my phone was off.

35:25.588 --> 35:26.827
I was with my dad.

35:27.641 --> 35:30.097
- Your dad?
- Yeah.

35:30.864 --> 35:32.191
I'm going home.

35:33.041 --> 35:34.423
It's over, Billy.

35:34.543 --> 35:36.133
We might as well take Ben's offer.

35:36.158 --> 35:37.962
I wrote the statement of claim,

35:38.006 --> 35:40.641
in case you run out of toilet paper.

35:45.607 --> 35:47.093
I don't buy it.

35:48.973 --> 35:51.086
You were so sure. You convinced me.

35:51.293 --> 35:53.470
We both saw those barrels
being pulled from the field.

35:53.495 --> 35:55.556
We can't link
those barrels to the mill.

35:55.591 --> 35:57.616
We have the chemical profile!

35:57.682 --> 35:59.226
It's not enough.

36:00.106 --> 36:01.728
The guy who ran us off the road?

36:02.521 --> 36:03.660
He works for Ben.

36:03.699 --> 36:05.566
Beckbie arrested him.

36:07.736 --> 36:11.638
No. A threat isn't proof of anything.

36:14.088 --> 36:16.022
Joanna, the girls need you.

36:16.328 --> 36:19.127
- We can't with this without you.
- But there's nothing to win.

36:19.207 --> 36:21.648
You heard the mayor.
She wants to take Ben's offer.

36:21.717 --> 36:23.963
That's the best we're gonna get.

36:25.230 --> 36:26.636
This isn't over,

36:26.661 --> 36:29.658
- not by a long shot.
- Billy...

36:34.010 --> 36:37.577
You must be her. Can't say
I see the resemblance.

36:39.277 --> 36:41.012
I'm sorry. Do we know each other?

36:41.037 --> 36:42.970
No, but I know your dad.

36:43.307 --> 36:45.539
Gerrilyn. What're you doing here?

36:46.108 --> 36:47.474
You're Luna's mom.

36:48.063 --> 36:49.910
- Is she OK?
- She's fine.

36:50.365 --> 36:52.079
Heard you took her to my mother's.

36:53.242 --> 36:54.523
Yeah...

36:54.576 --> 36:56.456
It seemed very important to her.

36:56.630 --> 36:58.719
So you met the whole family.

36:59.020 --> 37:00.520
They, uh, nice to you?

37:01.008 --> 37:02.393
'Cause we're not on the best of terms.

37:02.417 --> 37:04.257
Gerrilyn, is there something
we can do for you?

37:04.426 --> 37:06.460
I don't want Luna
working for you anymore.

37:06.789 --> 37:08.795
You need to stay away from her!

37:08.890 --> 37:10.431
And you can tell him it's
too little, too late.

37:10.455 --> 37:12.005
He can't get to her through you.

37:12.030 --> 37:13.639
Who are you talking about?

37:14.304 --> 37:16.003
My mom didn't tell you?

37:16.498 --> 37:18.331
Tell me what?

37:23.478 --> 37:26.646
That kid you were driving around?

37:27.367 --> 37:29.069
She's your sister.

37:31.500 --> 37:33.127
What are you talking about?

37:33.813 --> 37:36.027
I'm surprised he's never mentioned us.

37:36.471 --> 37:38.505
He talked about you all the time.

37:40.248 --> 37:42.270
OK. I think it's time for you to go.

37:42.365 --> 37:43.678
She's the one who should go!

37:43.703 --> 37:46.278
- Hey. Come on. That's enough.
- Nobody wants you here.

37:46.358 --> 37:48.068
Luna is mine.

37:48.325 --> 37:49.970
You stay the hell away from us.

37:50.865 --> 37:52.725
[DOOR BELL JINGLING]

37:54.308 --> 37:56.109
[DOOR CLOSING]

38:00.182 --> 38:02.583
[TENSE MUSIC]

38:04.084 --> 38:05.317
Could it be true?

38:09.258 --> 38:10.631
No.

38:13.548 --> 38:15.582
He never mentioned Gerrilyn?

38:19.268 --> 38:21.234
- Or another woman?
- No.

38:23.446 --> 38:24.698
Why would she make it up?

38:24.766 --> 38:26.799
I don't know.

38:31.671 --> 38:32.964
Could this have something to do

38:32.989 --> 38:35.052
